 {"id":"bd-2dow.4","title":"Implement MeasurableWidget for Complex Widgets (List, Table, Tabs)","description":"## Goal
Implement MeasurableWidget for complex, composed widgets that aggregate child sizes.

## Widgets in Scope (Full List)
1. **List/StatefulList** - Height = sum of item heights, width = max item width
2. **Table** - Column widths + row heights with header
3. **Tabs** - Tab bar height + content area
4. **Scrollable** - Viewport vs content size distinction
5. **Split/Pane** - Divider overhead + child sizes
6. **Canvas** - Fixed braille cell dimensions
7. **Sparkline** - Fixed height, variable width
8. **BarChart** - Bar count × bar width
9. **Gauge/LineGauge** - Fixed height, fills width

## Implementation Details

### List (Vertical Aggregation)
```rust
impl<T: MeasurableWidget> MeasurableWidget for List<'_, T> {
    fn measure(&self, available: Size) -> SizeConstraints {
        if self.items.is_empty() {
            return SizeConstraints::ZERO;
        }

        // Measure all items (cache results to avoid re-measure)
        let item_constraints: Vec<SizeConstraints> = self.items.iter()
            .map(|item| item.measure(available))
            .collect();

        // Width: max of all items
        let min_width = item_constraints.iter().map(|c| c.min.width).max().unwrap_or(0);
        let pref_width = item_constraints.iter().map(|c| c.preferred.width).max().unwrap_or(0);

        // Height: sum of all items
        let min_height = item_constraints.iter().map(|c| c.min.height).sum();
        let pref_height = item_constraints.iter().map(|c| c.preferred.height).sum();

        SizeConstraints {
            min: Size::new(min_width, min_height.min(available.height)), // Can scroll
            preferred: Size::new(pref_width, pref_height),
            max: None, // Lists can grow indefinitely
        }
    }

    fn has_intrinsic_size(&self) -> bool { \!self.items.is_empty() }
}
```

### Table (Grid Aggregation)
```rust
impl MeasurableWidget for Table<'_> {
    fn measure(&self, available: Size) -> SizeConstraints {
        let col_count = self.widths.len();
        let row_count = self.rows.len();

        // Phase 1: Measure columns (max cell width per column)
        let mut col_widths: Vec<u16> = vec\![0; col_count];

        // Header widths
        if let Some(header) = &self.header {
            for (i, cell) in header.cells.iter().enumerate() {
                let c = cell.measure(Size::MAX);
                col_widths[i] = col_widths[i].max(c.preferred.width);
            }
        }

        // Data cell widths
        for row in &self.rows {
            for (i, cell) in row.cells.iter().enumerate() {
                let c = cell.measure(Size::MAX);
                col_widths[i] = col_widths[i].max(c.preferred.width);
            }
        }

        // Phase 2: Calculate total dimensions
        let separator_width = if self.column_spacing > 0 { 
            (col_count - 1) as u16 * self.column_spacing 
        } else { 0 };

        let total_width: u16 = col_widths.iter().sum::<u16>() + separator_width;
        let row_height = 1u16; // Assume single-line rows for now
        let total_height = row_count as u16 + if self.header.is_some() { 1 } else { 0 };

        SizeConstraints {
            min: Size::new(col_count as u16, 1), // At least column count
            preferred: Size::new(total_width, total_height),
            max: Some(Size::new(total_width, total_height)), // Fixed content
        }
    }
}
```

### Tabs (Header + Content)
```rust
impl MeasurableWidget for Tabs<'_> {
    fn measure(&self, available: Size) -> SizeConstraints {
        // Tab bar: sum of tab title widths + separators
        let tab_bar_width: u16 = self.titles.iter()
            .map(|t| t.width() as u16 + 3) // " | " separator
            .sum();
        let tab_bar_height = 1u16;

        // Content area: active tab's content
        let content_constraints = self.content
            .as_ref()
            .map(|c| c.measure(Size::new(available.width, available.height.saturating_sub(tab_bar_height))))
            .unwrap_or(SizeConstraints::ZERO);

        SizeConstraints {
            min: Size::new(
                tab_bar_width.max(content_constraints.min.width),
                tab_bar_height + content_constraints.min.height,
            ),
            preferred: Size::new(
                tab_bar_width.max(content_constraints.preferred.width),
                tab_bar_height + content_constraints.preferred.height,
            ),
            max: content_constraints.max.map(|m| Size::new(
                tab_bar_width.max(m.width),
                tab_bar_height + m.height,
            )),
        }
    }
}
```

### Scrollable (Viewport vs Content)
```rust
impl<T: MeasurableWidget> MeasurableWidget for Scrollable<T> {
    fn measure(&self, _available: Size) -> SizeConstraints {
        // Report CONTENT size - layout system clamps to viewport
        let content = self.content.measure(Size::MAX);

        SizeConstraints {
            min: Size::new(3, 3), // Minimum for scrollbars
            preferred: content.preferred, // Would like full content visible
            max: None, // Can scroll to any content size
        }
    }
}
```

### Canvas (Braille Grid)
```rust
impl MeasurableWidget for Canvas {
    fn measure(&self, _available: Size) -> SizeConstraints {
        // Each terminal cell = 2x4 braille dots
        let cells_wide = (self.width + 1) / 2;
        let cells_tall = (self.height + 3) / 4;

        SizeConstraints {
            min: Size::new(1, 1),
            preferred: Size::new(cells_wide as u16, cells_tall as u16),
            max: Some(Size::new(cells_wide as u16, cells_tall as u16)),
        }
    }
}
```

