 {"id":"bd-2dow.5","title":"Measure Cache: Memoization + Invalidation Strategy","description":"## Goal
Cache measure() results to avoid redundant computation during layout, with correct invalidation when content changes.

## Background
measure() can be expensive for complex widgets (Tables with many cells, Lists with dynamic content). During a single layout pass, the same widget may be queried multiple times with the same available size. Caching eliminates this redundancy.

## Cache Design
```rust
use std::collections::HashMap;
use std::hash::{Hash, Hasher, DefaultHasher};

/// Unique identifier for a widget instance
#[derive(Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash, Debug)]
pub struct WidgetId(u64);

impl WidgetId {
    /// Create from memory address (stable for lifetime of widget)
    pub fn from_ptr<T>(ptr: &T) -> Self {
        Self(ptr as *const T as u64)
    }

    /// Create from content hash (stable across recreations)
    pub fn from_hash<T: Hash>(value: &T) -> Self {
        let mut hasher = DefaultHasher::new();
        value.hash(&mut hasher);
        Self(hasher.finish())
    }
}

/// Cache key: widget identity + available size
#[derive(Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
struct CacheKey {
    widget_id: WidgetId,
    available: Size,
}

/// Cached measurement result
struct CacheEntry {
    constraints: SizeConstraints,
    generation: u64,
    access_count: u32, // For LRU eviction
}

/// Thread-local measure cache
pub struct MeasureCache {
    entries: HashMap<CacheKey, CacheEntry>,
    generation: u64,
    max_entries: usize,
    hits: u64,
    misses: u64,
}

impl MeasureCache {
    pub fn new(max_entries: usize) -> Self {
        Self {
            entries: HashMap::with_capacity(max_entries),
            generation: 0,
            max_entries,
            hits: 0,
            misses: 0,
        }
    }

    /// Get cached result or compute and cache
    pub fn get_or_compute<F>(
        &mut self,
        widget_id: WidgetId,
        available: Size,
        compute: F,
    ) -> SizeConstraints
    where
        F: FnOnce() -> SizeConstraints,
    {
        let key = CacheKey { widget_id, available };

        if let Some(entry) = self.entries.get_mut(&key) {
            if entry.generation == self.generation {
                self.hits += 1;
                entry.access_count += 1;
                return entry.constraints;
            }
        }

        self.misses += 1;
        let constraints = compute();

        // Evict if at capacity
        if self.entries.len() >= self.max_entries {
            self.evict_lru();
        }

        self.entries.insert(key, CacheEntry {
            constraints,
            generation: self.generation,
            access_count: 1,
        });

        constraints
    }

    /// Invalidate all entries (bump generation)
    pub fn invalidate_all(&mut self) {
        self.generation = self.generation.wrapping_add(1);
    }

    /// Invalidate entries for specific widget
    pub fn invalidate_widget(&mut self, widget_id: WidgetId) {
        self.entries.retain(|k, _| k.widget_id != widget_id);
    }

    /// Get cache statistics
    pub fn stats(&self) -> CacheStats {
        CacheStats {
            entries: self.entries.len(),
            hits: self.hits,
            misses: self.misses,
            hit_rate: if self.hits + self.misses > 0 {
                self.hits as f64 / (self.hits + self.misses) as f64
            } else {
                0.0
            },
        }
    }

    fn evict_lru(&mut self) {
        // Find entry with lowest access_count
        if let Some(key) = self.entries.iter()
            .min_by_key(|(_, e)| e.access_count)
            .map(|(k, _)| *k)
        {
            self.entries.remove(&key);
        }
    }
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct CacheStats {
    pub entries: usize,
    pub hits: u64,
    pub misses: u64,
    pub hit_rate: f64,
}
```

## Invalidation Strategies

### 1. Generation-Based (Primary)
Bump generation on any state change affecting layout:
```rust
impl Model for App {
    fn update(&mut self, msg: Msg) -> Cmd {
        match msg {
            Msg::DataChanged(data) => {
                self.data = data;
                self.measure_cache.invalidate_all();
            }
            Msg::Resize(_) => {
                // Size-keyed, so no invalidation needed!
            }
            Msg::ThemeChanged => {
                // Theme affects widget rendering, not measurement
                // No invalidation needed
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### 2. Widget-Specific Invalidation
When only one widget changes:
```rust
impl Model for App {
    fn update(&mut self, msg: Msg) -> Cmd {
        match msg {
            Msg::ListItemAdded(item) => {
                self.list.push(item);
                self.measure_cache.invalidate_widget(WidgetId::from_hash(&"list"));
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### 3. Content-Addressed (Automatic)
Use content hash as widget ID - same content = same measurement:
```rust
impl MeasurableWidget for Paragraph<'_> {
    fn widget_id(&self) -> WidgetId {
        WidgetId::from_hash(&self.text)
    }
}
```

## Integration with Layout

### In split_with_measurer
```rust
impl Layout {
    pub fn split_with_measurer<F>(
        &self,
        area: Rect,
        cache: &mut MeasureCache,
        measurer: F,
    ) -> Vec<Rect>
    where
        F: Fn(usize) -> (WidgetId, &dyn MeasurableWidget),
    {
        for (i, constraint) in self.constraints.iter().enumerate() {
